# Product Catalog

All product data in this project flows through `src/utils/ProductService.ts`. Do NOT invent product literals, hand-write SKUs, hardcode prices, or import `productCatalog.json` directly. Whenever a tile, card, carousel, PDP, search result, demo button, or example needs a product, fetch it from `ProductService`. The catalog is the single source of truth — it owns the names, SKUs, prices, ratings, badges, images, and category structure.

This rule is the data-side companion to `component-communication.mdc`. That file says how product cards bind to Store state. This file says where the product itself comes from.

## Import

```tsx
import {
  getAllProducts,
  getProductBySku,
  getProductsByCategory,
  getProductsBySubcategory,
  getCategories,
  searchProducts,
  getHeroBanners,
  getMarketingTiles,
  getCatalogStats,
  type Product,
  type Category,
} from "./utils/ProductService";
```

Adjust relative depth from your file location. Never reach past `ProductService` to read `productCatalog.json` yourself.

## Architecture

`ProductService` is the only contract pages and components should know about. The JSON file behind it is an implementation detail.

| Layer | What it does | When to use |
|-------|--------------|-------------|
| **Data file** (`src/data/productCatalog.json`) | Owns the catalog content | Edit when adding/changing products. Never imported elsewhere. |
| **Service** (`src/utils/ProductService.ts`) | Typed, in-memory access to products, categories, banners, stats | Always — every consumer goes through this |
| **Components** (`src/components/{components,patterns}/`) | Render a product visually | Pass a `Product` (or its fields) in; never invent product data inside |
| **Bindings** (`useStoreConnectedItemBindings` in `Store.tsx`) | Wire a rendered product to cart/heart state | See `component-communication.mdc` |

## CRITICAL: products come from `ProductService`, never inline

This is the rule the rest of the file expands on. Any time you need a product anywhere in the app, you pick it from the catalog.

```tsx
// CORRECT — pick a product from the catalog
const product = getProductBySku("asus-vivobook-go-15-ryzen5");
if (!product) return null;

<ProductCardGrid
  image={product.imageUrl}
  name={product.name}
  price={product.price}
  cents={product.cents}
  rating={product.rating}
  ratingCount={product.ratingCount}
  pickup={product.pickup}
  wasPrice={product.originalPrice ?? undefined}
  flag={product.flag ?? undefined}
/>
```

```tsx
// WRONG — invented product literal. Names, prices, SKUs, and images
// must not be hand-written. They drift from the catalog and break
// search, cart consistency, and Store bindings.
<ProductCardGrid
  image="https://example.com/blender.jpg"
  name="3-in-1 Blender"
  price="169"
  cents="98"
/>
```

```tsx
// WRONG — bypassing the service to read JSON directly.
// ProductService enriches each product with category context;
// raw JSON does not have categoryId/categoryName/etc.
import catalog from "../data/productCatalog.json";
const blender = catalog.categories[1].subcategories[1].items[0];
```

This applies to **every** surface — production pages, demo sections, Storybook examples, fixtures used in dev, anywhere a product appears. If the catalog doesn't have what you need, add it to `productCatalog.json`; do not work around the service.

## API

### Browsing

```tsx
const categories = getCategories();              // Category[]
const allProducts = getAllProducts();            // Product[]
const electronics = getProductsByCategory("electronics");
const laptops = getProductsBySubcategory("electronics", "laptops");
```

`Category` exposes `subcategories` (each with `products: Product[]`) and a flat `allProducts: Product[]`. Use these — do not flatten subcategories yourself.

### Lookup

```tsx
const product = getProductBySku("asus-vivobook-go-15-ryzen5");
if (!product) return null; // sku not in catalog
```

`getProductBySku` returns `Product | undefined`. Always handle the undefined case rather than non-null-asserting.

### Search

```tsx
const results = searchProducts(query);   // case-insensitive substring on product name
```

Empty/whitespace query returns every product. The Store search query event is independent — see `component-communication.mdc` for `useSharedSearchQuery()`.

### Stats

```tsx
const { totalProducts, totalCategories, totalSubcategories, ebtEligibleCount } = getCatalogStats();
```

Use this for catalog overview UIs. Never count `getAllProducts().length` inline if a stat already covers it.

### Hero banners & marketing tiles

```tsx
const banners = getHeroBanners();    // HeroBanner[]
const tiles = getMarketingTiles();   // MarketingTile[]
```

These are catalog content too — same rule applies. Don't hand-author banner or tile literals; edit `productCatalog.json`.

## Product shape

```ts
interface Product {
  sku: string;            // unique identifier — the key for Store bindings
  name: string;
  price: string;          // dollar portion as a string, e.g. "299"
  cents: string;          // cents portion as a string, e.g. "00"
  priceCents: number;     // integer cents — the value used by cart math
  originalPrice: string | null;
  rating: number;         // 0–5
  ratingCount: string;    // formatted, e.g. "10,747"
  imageUrl: string;       // resolved CDN URL
  badge: { label: string; type: string } | null;
  pickup: string;         // e.g. "Free shipping, arrives tomorrow"
  ebt: boolean;
  flag: string | null;
  categoryId: string;
  categoryName: string;
  subcategoryId: string;
  subcategoryName: string;
}
```

`price` / `cents` are split because the design renders the dollar and cent portions at different sizes. `priceCents` is the value to pass into Store cart operations.

## Wiring a product into the UI

Once you have a `Product`, bind it to the Store using the pattern in `component-communication.mdc`. The two rules compose: `ProductService` gives you the product, `useStoreConnectedItemBindings` keeps it in sync with the cart and favorites.

```tsx
import { useStoreConnectedItemBindings } from "./utils/Store";
import { getProductBySku } from "./utils/ProductService";

function FeaturedProduct() {
  const product = getProductBySku("asus-vivobook-go-15-ryzen5");
  const bindings = useStoreConnectedItemBindings()({
    sku: product!.sku,
    name: product!.name,
    priceCents: product!.priceCents,
  });

  return (
    <ProductCardGrid
      image={product!.imageUrl}
      name={product!.name}
      price={product!.price}
      cents={product!.cents}
      rating={product!.rating}
      ratingCount={product!.ratingCount}
      pickup={product!.pickup}
      hearted={bindings.hearted}
      onHeartChange={bindings.onHeartChange}
      cartQty={bindings.cartQty}
      onCartQtyChange={bindings.onCartQtyChange}
      onAddToCart={bindings.onAddToCart}
    />
  );
}
```

For details on `addToCart` vs `setCartQty`, the binding shape, and PDP composition, read `component-communication.mdc`. Do not restate or re-implement those rules here.

## Hard Constraints

- MUST source every product from `ProductService` — `getProductBySku`, `getAllProducts`, `getProductsByCategory`, `getProductsBySubcategory`, `searchProducts`, or by iterating `getCategories()`.
- MUST source hero banners from `getHeroBanners()` and marketing tiles from `getMarketingTiles()`.
- MUST identify a product to the Store using `{ sku, name, priceCents }` taken **directly** from the `Product` returned by `ProductService` — never re-typed by hand.
- MUST add new products by editing `src/data/productCatalog.json`. The JSON is the only authoring surface.
- NEVER import `src/data/productCatalog.json` outside `ProductService.ts`.
- NEVER hand-write product names, SKUs, prices, images, ratings, or badges as inline literals — even in demos, examples, or fixtures.
- NEVER mock a `Product` with `{ sku: "demo-1", name: "Demo Item", priceCents: 999 }` for a card or tile. Pick a real product from the catalog instead.
- NEVER non-null-assert (`!`) the result of `getProductBySku` in production paths without first guarding against `undefined`.
- NEVER duplicate `ProductService` functionality — no parallel "product helpers" file, no per-page filtering helpers that re-implement `getProductsByCategory`.
- NEVER reach into `Subcategory.products` or `Category.allProducts` to invent your own flattening; use `getAllProducts` or `getProductsByCategory`.

## Intent → API map

| You want to… | Use this |
|---|---|
| Show one specific product (PDP, hero, featured) | `getProductBySku(sku)` |
| Show a product grid for a whole category | `getProductsByCategory(categoryId)` |
| Show a product grid for one subcategory | `getProductsBySubcategory(categoryId, subcategoryId)` |
| Show every product on the page | `getAllProducts()` |
| Power a search input | `searchProducts(query)` |
| Render a category navigation / filter bar | `getCategories()` |
| Render hero/banner content | `getHeroBanners()` |
| Render marketing tile content | `getMarketingTiles()` |
| Show counts in a stats strip | `getCatalogStats()` |
| Build a "flash deals" row | `getAllProducts().filter(p => p.originalPrice)` |

## Pre-Response Checklist

Before returning code that touches a product, confirm:

- [ ] Every product comes from `ProductService` — no inline `{ sku, name, priceCents }` literals.
- [ ] Hero banners and marketing tiles come from `getHeroBanners()` / `getMarketingTiles()`.
- [ ] `productCatalog.json` is not imported anywhere except `ProductService.ts`.
- [ ] `getProductBySku` results are guarded for `undefined` before use.
- [ ] Store identity (`{ sku, name, priceCents }`) is read straight off the `Product`, not retyped.
- [ ] Category/subcategory traversal uses `getCategories()` shapes, not hand-rolled flattening.
- [ ] No competing "product helpers" file is being introduced.
- [ ] If new products were needed, they were added to `productCatalog.json` rather than inlined in code.
